MODULE
  windows - Message and Dialog Boxes on Windows

INTRODUCTION
  This module provides functions  for using  message and dialog
  boxes as well as to access the clipboard from within MuPAD on
  Windows operating systems.

INTERFACE
  windows::alert,      windows::beep,    windows::box,
  windows::clipboard,  windows::doc,     windows::error,
  windows::message,    windows::pause,   windows::question,
  windows::selectFile, windows::warning, windows::winHelp
<!-- BEGIN-FUNC alert -->
NAME
  windows::alert - Plays an alert sound

SYNOPSIS
  windows::alert()
  windows::alert( style )

PARAMETERS
  style - Identifier, one of: Message, Error, Warning, Question
          or an integer which specifies a registered sound

DESCRIPTION
  The function plays the specified waveform sound  using the PC
  soundcard. If no soundcard is installed a simple message beep
  is played using the computer speaker.

EXAMPLES
  >> windows::alert()
  >> windows::alert( Message  )
  >> windows::alert( Error    )
  >> windows::alert( Warning  )
  >> windows::alert( Question )

SEE ALSO
  windows::error, windows::message, windows::question,
  windows::selectFile, windows::warning
<!-- END-FUNC -->
<!-- BEGIN-FUNC beep -->
NAME
  windows::beep - Plays a tone of a given frequnce

SYNOPSIS
  windows::beep( frequence, duration )

PARAMETERS
  frequence - typically between 100 an 10.000 Hertz
  duration  - specified in milli seconds

DESCRIPTION
  The function plays the specified frequence for the specified
  duration using the computer speaker.

EXAMPLES
  >> windows::beep(500+k*100,100) $ k=1..10 
  ...
  
  >>(windows::beep(500+k*100,100),windows::pause(100)) $ k=1..10
  ...

SEE ALSO
  windows::alert, windows::pause
<!-- END-FUNC -->
<!-- BEGIN-FUNC box -->
NAME
  windows::box - Displays a windows free style message box

SYNOPSIS
  windows::box( title, text, flags )

PARAMETERS
  title - String, the title of the message box
  text  - String, the message to be displayed
  flags - Integer, MessageBox style option (Win32)

DESCRIPTION
  The function displays a message box with the headline 'title'
  and the message 'text'. The icon as well as the buttons which
  are displayed  can be specified via the integer 'flags'.  The
  corresponding  integer codes  are described in the  Win32 SDK
  documentation of the Microsoft Visual C++ Compiler. The func-
  tion returns an integer  which indicates the button  that was
  pressed.

EXAMPLES
  >> MB_ABORTRETRYIGNORE := 2:
     MB_ICONERROR  := 16:
     MB_DEFBUTTON2 := 256:
     windows::box( "User-defined Free-style Box",
                   "Wizards can create free-style boxes",
                   MB_ABORTRETRYIGNORE+MB_ICONERROR+
                   MB_DEFBUTTON2
     );

SEE ALSO
  windows::alert, windows::clipboard, windows::error,
  windows::message, windows::selectFile, windows::warning
