<!-- BEGIN-FUNC question -->
NAME
  windows::question - Displays a question message box

SYNOPSIS
  windows::question( title, text )

PARAMETERS
  title - String, the title of the message box
  text  - String, the message to be displayed

DESCRIPTION
  The function displays a message box with the headline 'title'
  and the question 'text' with a question mark icon. It returns
  TRUE if the user clicks on the 'YES' button  and FALSE if the
  user clicks on the 'NO' button.   If the box is destroyed and
  neither 'YES' nor 'NO' was clicked,  the function returns the
  the boolean value UNKNOWN.

EXAMPLES
  >> windows::question( "It큦 a Question", "Do you like it?" )

SEE ALSO
  windows::alert, windows::box, windows::clipboard,
  windows::error, windows::message, windows::selectFile,
  windows::warning
