<!-- BEGIN-FUNC selectFile -->
NAME
  selectFile - Displays a windows file dialog

SYNOPSIS
  windows::selectFile()

DESCRIPTION
  The function displays  a common file dialog box  which allows
  the user to browse directories and to select a file. The full
  pathname of the selected file is returned.  If the dialog box
  is destroyed or the dialog is canceled and no file was selec-
  ted then the empty string is returned.

EXAMPLES
  >> windows::selectFile()

     "MuPAD.hlp"

SEE ALSO
  warning,::alert, windows::clipboard, windows::error,
  windows::message, windows::question, windows::warning
