<!-- BEGIN-FUNC winHelp -->
NAME
  windows::winHelp - Opens the Windows help file browser

SYNOPSIS
  windows::winHelp( helpfile, command, data )

PARAMETERS
  helpfile - String, pathname of a Windows help file
  command  - Identifier, one of: Index, Key, PartialKey, Quit,
             Contents, Finder
  data     - String, a keyword, depends on 'command'

DESCRIPTION
  The function opens  the Windows help browser  with the  given
  help file  and displays the information specified via the pa-
  rameters 'command' and 'data'. If the command 'Quit' is used,
  the help browser is closed. Details can be found in the Win32
  SDK documentation of the Microsoft Visual C++ Compiler.   The
  function returns TRUE if it was successful.  It returns FALSE
  otherwise.

EXAMPLES
  >> windows::winHelp( windows::selectFile(), Index, "" )

  >> windows::winHelp( windows::selectFile(), Key, "" )

SEE ALSO
  windows::error, windows::message, windows::question,
  windows::selectFile, windows::warning
